What are the causes of acne?

Acne or pimples are common skin problems and are a result of the malfunctioning of the sebaceous glands in your skin. The sebaceous glands are responsible to produce sebuum, which is also known as oil. Excessive sebuum production is a major cause of acne. The glands get clogged up when the excess oil mixes with dead skin cells and bacteria and this leads to the appearance of pimples and blackheads.

Acné can be triggered by various factors. Here are some of the common causes of acne:

* Excessive oily sebuum
* Hormonal changes
* Stress

बाप ने बड़े बेटे संग मिलकर छोटे बेटे को दी दिल दहला देने वाली मौत, जानिए वजह (Video)

हट, स्ट्रीट लाइट, साइन बोर्ड, अतिरिक्त पार्किंग स्टाल, ट्राफिक साइनेज और रेस्टोरेंट की सुविधाएं भी होंगी।
